# ImGui

## Purpose
Provides an `ImGuiLayer` overlay that initialises Dear ImGui, wires it to the Win32 window and
DirectX 11 device, and brackets each frame with `NewFrame`/`Render` calls. ECS systems issue
widget calls from within their `Update()` methods — `ImGuiLayer` handles all frame lifecycle
automatically.

Excluded from Testing builds via `#ifndef TESTS_ENABLED` in `Application::Init()`.

## Integration Points

- `ImGuiLayer` is pushed as an overlay (after all regular layers) during `Application::Init()`.
- `Application::Update()` calls `Begin()` before `OnUpdate` and `End()` after — all
  system `Update()` calls fall inside the open Dear ImGui frame.
- Input is captured at the Win32 `WndProc` level by `imgui_impl_win32`; ImGui input does not
  pass through the engine event bus and does not appear in `InputStateSingletonComponent`.

## Usage from ECS Systems

Include `<imgui.h>` and issue widget calls inside `System::Update()` between
`ImGui::Begin(...)`/`ImGui::End()` pairs. Do not call `ImGui::NewFrame()` or
`ImGui::Render()` — the layer owns those boundaries.

